claim.claim-text:
1. A method of paying medical claims comprising:
using one or more processors:
a) receiving payer payment method preferences which include a preferred order of payment methods to payees;
b) formatting a payment to one of the payees including:
a consolidated financial instrument which transfers accumulated monies without co-mingling funds in compliance with ERISA regulations; and
at least one explanation of benefits associated with the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits includes a patient identification, a payer identification, a service provider identification, a date of service, a service identification, a patient obligation and an amount paid;

c) sending the formatted payment by the preferred method to the one of the payees with a coordinated transfer of the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits;
d) determining an acceptance or a rejection of the sent formatted payment to the one of the payees;
e) automatically repeating steps b)-d) for subsequent method preferences in the payer preference order by a cost of a transaction using the payment method until the transfer is accepted by the one of the payees; and
f) recording acceptance of the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits to the one of the payees in a data store.

3. The method of paying medical claims according to claim 1, wherein the financial instrument includes at least one of:
a direct deposit transaction;
a bank wire transfer;
a bank draft;
a credit card payment; and
an automated clearinghouse (ACH) transaction.

4. The method of paying medical claims according to claim 1, wherein the at least one associated explanation of benefits includes at least one format of:
an ANSI 835 electronic formatted transaction;
a PDF image;
a print image;
a provider portal format; and
a payee specified format.

6. The method of paying medical claims according to claim 1, further including:
using one or more processors:
receiving a rejection from the one of the payees for at least one payment method.

9. The method of paying medical claims according to claim 1, wherein the payment methods include:
a direct ACH provider payment and an associated at least one electronically formatted ANSI 835 explanation of benefits;
a stored value card payment and an associated at least one electronically formatted explanation of benefits;
a contracted ACH provider payment and an associated at least one electronically formatted ANSI 835 explanation of benefits; and
a provider draft payment and an associated at least one printed explanation of benefits.

11. The method of paying medical claims according to claim 1, further comprising:
in a payment computer memory, receiving and storing a payment and an associated at least one explanation of benefits for each of a plurality of batches of employer group payments;
with a computer sorting routine, in accordance with the received payment and explanation of benefits in the payment memory, making a series of funds transfers from each employer group settlement bank account individually to each of a plurality of corresponding service provider settlement bank accounts without co-mingling funds to accumulate monies in each payee settlement bank account;
for each of the received payment and the associated at least one explanation of benefits, translating the payment and the associated at least one explanation of benefits with a computer routine into an interpretation, and content compatible with each identified payee's accounting system.

12. A medical claims payment system comprising:
one or more servers configured to:
a) receive one or more payer payment method preferences which include a preferred order of payment methods to payees ordered by costs of transactions using the payment methods;
b) format a payment which includes:
a consolidated financial instrument which transfers accumulated monies without co-mingling funds in compliance with ERISA regulations; and
at least one explanation of benefits associated with the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits includes a patient identification, a payer identification, a service provider identification, a date of service, a service identification, a patient obligation, an adjustment and an amount paid;

c) send the payment formatted according to a most preferred, as determined by transaction cost, not rejected payment method to one of the payees with a coordinated transfer of the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits;
d) determine acceptance or rejection of the send payment to the one of the payees;
e) repeat steps b)-d) automatically using payment methods in the preferred order by the cost of transactions of the payment methods until the payment is accepted by the one of the payees; and
f) record acceptance of the payment to the one of the payees in a data store.

15. The medical claims payment system according to claim 12, wherein the payments include:
a direct ACH provider payment and an associated at least one electronically formatted ANSI 835 explanation of benefits;
a stored value card payment and an associated at least one electronically formatted explanation of benefits;
a contracted ACH provider payment and an associated at least one electronically formatted ANSI 835 explanation of benefits; and
a provider draft payment and an associated at least one printed explanation of benefits.

19. A medical claims system, comprising:
one or more servers configured to:
a) receive payer payment method preferences which include a preferred order of payment method to each payee;
b) automatically format a payment accepted-by the payee which includes:
a consolidated financial instrument which transfers accumulated monies without co-mingling funds in compliance with ERISA regulations; and
at least one explanation of benefits associated with the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits includes a patient identification, a payer identification, a service provider identification, at least one date of service and associated service identification, and an amount paid;

c) route the formatted payment to each payee with a coordinated transfer of the consolidated financial instrument and the at least one associated explanation of benefits;
d) in response to the formatted payment not being accepted by each payee, automatically resending the formatted payment using the payment method preferences based on a payment method transaction cost until accepted; and
e) record the acceptance of the consolidated financial instrument and the associated at least one associated explanation of benefits to each payee in a data store.
